RusTok Additional Use Grant

Subject to the Business Source License 1.1 terms above, RusTok may be used for free by individuals, independent developers, community projects, open-source projects, companies, agencies, startups, and organizations if their Total Finances do not exceed USD $3,000,000 during the most recent 12-month period.

"Total Finances" means the largest of: (a) aggregate gross revenue; (b) annual budget; or (c) total funding, investment, grants, or other financing received during the most recent 12-month period, including all entities under common control.

Free use under this Additional Use Grant includes development, testing, internal use, production use, commercial use, customer projects, module development, extension development, and use of RusTok as an internal component, backend, admin panel, workflow engine, commerce engine, marketplace engine, CMS, automation layer, infrastructure layer, or development framework for a distinct product or service.

A separate RusTok Commercial License is required for organizations with Total Finances above USD $3,000,000 and for production use, commercial use, SaaS use, hosted service use, managed service use, cloud service use, white-label use, resale, redistribution as a competing platform, use of RusTok as the basis for a competing product or service, offering RusTok itself as SaaS, offering a substantially similar hosted platform, offering managed RusTok hosting or managed RusTok service, offering white-label RusTok, selling access to RusTok as the main product, or using RusTok as the core of a competing commercial platform.

Allowed SaaS use: using RusTok as an internal component, backend, admin panel, workflow engine, commerce engine, marketplace engine, CMS, automation layer, infrastructure layer, or development framework for a distinct application, product, or service is permitted under this Additional Use Grant, provided that the user's organization does not exceed USD $3,000,000 Total Finances; the product or service is not RusTok itself; the product or service is not a substantially similar or competing platform; RusTok is not offered as a hosted RusTok platform, managed RusTok service, white-label RusTok product, or resale product; and all LICENSE, NOTICE, copyright notices, license notices, source code attribution notices, and license headers are preserved where required.

Restricted SaaS use: offering RusTok itself as SaaS, offering a substantially similar hosted platform, offering managed RusTok hosting or managed RusTok service, offering white-label RusTok, selling access to RusTok as the main product, or using RusTok as the core of a competing commercial platform requires a separate RusTok Commercial License or prior written permission from RusTokRs regardless of revenue.

The License and this Additional Use Grant apply to the Licensed Work as a whole and to any substantial portion, extracted component, module, package, copy, modification, or derivative work of the Licensed Work. A user may not avoid the License by copying only part of RusTok, renaming RusTok, extracting a module, embedding RusTok components into another product, removing RusTok notices, or using RusTok code inside a larger proprietary system. Production use of any substantial portion, extracted component, module, package, copy, modification, or derivative work of the Licensed Work is treated the same as production use of the Licensed Work. If the user's organization exceeds USD $3,000,000 Total Finances, such production use requires a separate RusTok Commercial License.

For customer projects, agency work, implementation services, outsourcing, consulting, integration, or development performed for a third party, the Total Finances threshold applies to both the service provider and the end customer or beneficial user. If either the service provider or the end customer or beneficial user exceeds USD $3,000,000 Total Finances, production, commercial, SaaS, hosted, managed service, cloud service, white-label, resale, or competing platform use requires a separate RusTok Commercial License.

The following is permitted under this Additional Use Grant and is not considered SaaS, hosted service, managed service, white-label use, or competing platform use: publishing an install script, Docker image, Helm chart, Terraform module, Ansible playbook, server image, marketplace image, or one-click installation package for RusTok; allowing users to deploy RusTok into their own cloud account, server, VPS, Kubernetes cluster, or infrastructure; and offering infrastructure hosting where the customer controls the RusTok instance, data, configuration, domain, users, and application lifecycle.

This infrastructure and marketplace distribution permission applies only if the distribution preserves LICENSE, NOTICE, copyright notices, license notices, source code attribution notices, and license headers where present; RusTok is not renamed or presented as the provider's own product; RusTok is not offered as a white-label product; the provider does not operate RusTok as a managed application service for third parties; the provider does not sell RusTok itself as a hosted or managed RusTok service; the customer remains responsible for operating and administering the deployed RusTok instance; and the customer's own use of RusTok remains subject to the RusTok license terms, including the Total Finances threshold and Commercial License requirements.

Applications, modules, plugins, themes, integrations, and services built on top of RusTok public APIs are not considered derivative works of RusTok solely because they use those public APIs, unless they copy, modify, embed, or include substantial portions of RusTok source code.

No frontend "Powered by RusTok" attribution, logo attribution, footer attribution, login-screen attribution, or mandatory links to the RusTok website are required. The attribution requirement applies only to copyright notices, license notices, source code attribution notices, LICENSE files, NOTICE files, and license headers where present in source code. All copyright notices, license notices, source code attribution notices, and license headers included in the Licensed Work must be preserved in all copies, modifications, derivative works, extracted components, modules, packages, and substantial portions of the Licensed Work. Removing, obscuring, rewriting, or materially altering RusTok copyright notices, license notices, source code attribution notices, or license headers is not permitted unless expressly allowed by a separate written RusTok Commercial License.
